        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Since $f$ is even, $f(4) = f(-4) = 12$. Thus $2(12) - 5 = 19$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the jump at $x=1$ for $f(x) = \\begin{cases} 2x + 3 & x \\le 1 \\\\ 8 - x & x > 1 \\end{cases}$ (Limit from right minus limit from left).",
        "options": ["$2$", "$5$", "$7$", "$-2$"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Left limit: $2(1)+3 = 5$. Right limit: $8-1 = 7$. Jump $= 7 - 5 = 2$."
      },
